idCitation.resTitle: NUTS regions and boundaries Link table at 60M scale

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This table is an attribute table to identify the NUTS Boundaries from the feature class NUTS_BN_60M_2010 that make up a specific NUTS region in the feature class NUTS_RG_60M_2010 (topological relationship table between regions and boundaries of the NUTS_2010 60M dataset).
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This table forms the link between the feature classes NUTS_RG_60M_2010 and NUTS_BN_60M_2010. The M-N relationship between the feature classes becomes 1-M and N-1 through this table. For each NUTS region you can identify the boundaries it is made of and for each boundary line you can identify the regions that are on both sides of the border.

dataLineage.statement:
This dataset (together with the other datasets: NUTS_2010, CNTR_2010, COMM_2010, EEZ_2010 and COAS_2010) is based on geometry of EBM_v5 of EuroGeographics on commune level with a resolution of 30m (scale 1:100.000) enriched with some other datasources like Gaul 2008 country data and ArcWorld data. This resulted in a common repository of geometry of which the different datasets were derived. The different scale levels were derived of generalizations of the common repository on 100K scale. This means that within each scale level the feature classes of all these datasets: COMM_2010, NUTS_2010, CNTR_2010 and COAS_2010, are fully coherent and compliant.
The NUTS_2010 dataset consists of 2 feature classes (regions labels and boundaries) per scale level (100k, 1M, 3M, 10M, 20M, 60M).
The boundaries and regions are related to each other through a relationship table. The 5 small scale feature classes should be used exclusively for cartographic purposes. Apart from the 12 above mentioned feature classes there is also a label feature class (scale independent). This labelpoint feature class was created with a label inside each NUTS region at the 4 NUTS levels (0 - 3).
In addition two line feature classes were created: one feature class for cartograhic joiners to identify where NUTS areas have one or more enclaves and a second line feature class for cartographic separators, to identify where the NUTS limits are in the archipelagos. The arcs of two latter feature classes are only useful for cartographic purposes and are not meant to identify actual administrative or statistical boundaries stretching into the sea or any other significance. The extent of this feature class is EU27, EFTA and Croatia, FYROM and Turkey.

prcStep.description: For each NUTS region (all 4 subclasses) in the feature class NUTS_RG_60M_2010 the bordering lines in the feature class NUTS_BN_60M_2010 were identified by making use of a spatial selection. This result was written to the NUTS_RG_BN_60M_2010.

dataSource.srcDesc:
(i) Eurogeographics EBM v5.0.(scale 1:100K) (ii) GAUL 2008 country level data (iii) NSI of TR for the Turkish features (v) GRO (General Register Office for Scotland) -- for scale level 100K (vi) NUTS nomenclature supplied by EUROSTAT -- for all scale levels
This feature class is created from a generalization of this common repository
